init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You notice that your siblings are starting to look… different.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The people you grew up seeing every day are starting to disappear.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're thinning hair, your skin is sagging and wrinkles are beginning to appear.

actions.text: You notice that your siblings are starting to look… different. There is something off, it's almost an aura around those that received the immortality treatment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Your doctor tells you that it's something they've been seeing more and more, but that it's nothing to worry about.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A young, healthy man is limping down the street with what appears to be a shattered leg.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: thick black smoke emanates from his leg.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But you see them dying all around you.
